<p>Source: International Trade Centre, « Trade Map ».</p><p><b>1.3 Situating regional agricultural trade policy</b></p><p>Regional policy coordination takes place through several organisations. The 19-member COMESA and 15-member SADC are both implementing FTAs and pursuing plans for customs unions. In addition there is already a customs union in existence, formed by the 5-member EAC.</p><p><b>Table 2: ESA countries’ overlapping membership of regional groupings</b></p><table class="renderedtable" border="1" cellpadding="2" cellspacing="0">
